    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "After some second thoughts, why not restrict the scope of this function to only the `items` provided prop as it will be for now only used when filtering or sorting `items`.\r\n\r\nThe api will become: \r\n\r\nwe had a prop called `transformItems`. It will take the `items` as a parameter, and expect in return the same `items` structure.\r\nThis props, if exists, will be called each time a connector called its `getProvidedProps` function.\r\nWill only be available on widgets that have an `items` provided props. \r\n\r\nex of usage:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n<RefinementList attributeName=\"category\" \t\r\n\t\t\t\ttransformItems={items => {\r\n      \t\t\t\treturn orderBy(items, ['label'], ['asc']);\r\n\t\t\t\t}}\r\n/>\r\n```\r\n",
    "created_at": "2017-01-05T14:20:14Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1806#issuecomment-270654244",
    "id": 270654244,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1806",
    "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI3MDY1NDI0NA==",
